<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1112" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1112">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17022.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Barnum</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of War</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort Sam Houston</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Following received from General Pershing: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Squad of Mexicans appeared this afternoon half mile east of
                                    international bridge, deliberately fired towards American side,
                                    killing railroad car inspector. <pb facs="0937" n="821" xml:id="pg_821"/> There had been little firing and none
                                    toward American side. Am now covering whole river front, and
                                    troops have orders to vigorously return any deliberate firing
                                    from Mexican side.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnum.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>